# Environment Variables - OPTIONAL for this project
# 
# This WordPress + MySQL project has all credentials hardcoded in docker-compose.yml
# for simplicity and beginner-friendly setup.
#
# .env file is NOT required to run this project.
#
# However, for PRODUCTION use, you should externalize sensitive data:
# 1. Create a .env file (copy this file and rename to .env)
# 2. Uncomment and set the values below
# 3. Update docker-compose.yml to reference these variables using ${VARIABLE_NAME}
#
# Example Production Configuration:
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=your_secure_root_password
# MYSQL_DATABASE=wordpress_db
# MYSQL_USER=wordpress_user
# MYSQL_PASSWORD=your_secure_wordpress_password
# WORDPRESS_PORT=8080
#
# Then in docker-compose.yml, replace hardcoded values with:
# MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: ${MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD}
# MYSQL_DATABASE: ${MYSQL_DATABASE}
# etc.
